snippet: The unrest stems from longstanding disputes between the native Berbers and Arab settlers over land and housing.
abstract: Clashes between native Berbers and Arab settlers in Algerian province of Ghardaia, over land and housing disputes, results in at least 18 deaths.
lead_paragraph: The unrest stems from longstanding disputes between the native Berbers and Arab settlers over land and housing.

headline.main: Berbers and Arabs Clash in Algeria, Leaving at Least 18 Dead
headline.print_headline: Africa; Algeria: At Least 18 Die as Berbers and Arabs Clash
